        "title": "feat(context-engine): pass runtime settings into lifecycle",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAI-assisted change: yes. Forge/Codex produced the implementation and PR shepherding with OpenAI `gpt-5.5`; ragesaq reviewed the direction and required production-grade proof before merge.\n\nPass a typed `ContextEngineRuntimeSettings` contract through the context-engine lifecycle for embedded, CLI, and Codex app-server runs. Context engines now receive a versioned snapshot of runtime mode, model/provider state, host capabilities, token limits, and diagnostics instead of only the assemble-time `model` string.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `ContextEngineRuntimeSettings` and `ContextEngineRuntimeMode` in `src/context-engine/types.ts`.\n- Add `buildContextEngineRuntimeSettings()` in `src/context-engine/runtime-settings.ts`.\n- Thread `runtimeSettings` through bootstrap, assemble, afterTurn, compact, and maintenance paths.\n- Export the runtime-settings contract and errors through the public plugin SDK barrel.\n- Preserve strict legacy context engines: if an engine rejects `runtimeSettings` as an unknown key, OpenClaw retries the lifecycle call without it instead of quarantining the engine.\n- Document the public context-engine runtime-settings contract in `docs/concepts/context-engine.md` and `docs/plugins/sdk-overview.md`.\n- Update the plugin SDK export contract test for the new public runtime-settings error exports.\n\n## Current Head\n\nCurrent PR head: `5ea3873f0039c1eff0eb22ee0aa619af6797e4fa`.\n\nThis branch currently includes Anvil's unrelated Gemini model-id commit `747f09e19610`. I did not force-rewrite or remove another agent's commit without operator approval, so this PR is still broader than the runtime-settings branch should ideally be.\n\n## Review Findings Addressed\n\n- [P1] Strict-schema legacy engines could quarantine on the new `runtimeSettings` key. Fixed by adding `runtimeSettings` to the registry legacy strip/retry set for bootstrap, maintain, afterTurn, assemble, and compact. Covered by focused compatibility tests. Commit: `4e201a70e7`.\n- [P2] `model.family` could mirror a concrete model id. Fixed by defaulting family to `null` unless a real family is supplied. Covered by regression tests. Commits: `6cd24ab8fd`, `c4f5d721ff`.\n- [P2] SDK contract was exported but not documented. Fixed by documenting `runtimeSettings` in context-engine docs and SDK overview. Commit: `4e201a70e7`.\n- [P2] `compact()` documented `runtimeSettings`, but real compact callers did not pass it. Fixed embedded timeout/overflow compaction, queued/manual embedded compaction, CLI compaction, and follow-up maintenance to pass typed runtime settings. Commit: `5ea3873f00`.\n- [P2] Production embedded paths did not populate requested/resolved/fallback/degraded fields. Fixed embedded attempts to capture requested model and pass fallback metadata through bootstrap, assemble, afterTurn, and maintenance. Commit: `5ea3873f00`.\n- CI failure in `checks-fast-contracts-plugins-b`: fixed `src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-index.test.ts` to include `ContextEngineRuntimeSettingsUnavailableError` and `ContextEngineRuntimeSettingsUnsupportedError`. Commit: `5ea3873f00`.\n- Copilot: `fallbackReason` and `fallbackActive` could be inconsistent. Fixed by deriving `fallbackActive` from any non-empty fallback reason. Covered by regression test. Commit: `4e201a70e7`.\n- Copilot: runtime-settings Error subclasses lacked names. Fixed. Commit: `6cd24ab8fd`.\n- Copilot: missing builder test branches for degraded mode and invalid capabilities. Fixed. Commit: `4e201a70e7`.\n\n## Current-Head Proof\n\nEnvironment: OpenClaw source tree for this PR branch, run locally against current head `5ea3873f0039c1eff0eb22ee0aa619af6797e4fa`. Proof output is sanitized: no home paths, tokens, private endpoints, or raw transcripts are included here.\n\nCommands run at current head:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-index.test.ts src/context-engine/context-engine.test.ts src/context-engine/runtime-settings.test.ts src/agents/harness/context-engine-lifecycle.test.ts\npnpm check:test-types\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.contracts-plugin.config.ts --maxWorkers=1\npnpm build\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nObserved result:\n\n```text\nplugin-sdk-index.test.ts: 4 passed\ncontext-engine.test.ts: 42 passed\nruntime-settings.test.ts: 6 passed\ncontext-engine-lifecycle.test.ts: 11 passed\npnpm check:test-types: exit 0\ncontracts-plugin config: 64 files, 893 tests passed\npnpm build: exit 0, including check-plugin-sdk-exports OK\ngit diff --check: clean\n```\n\nCompatibility proof added in `context-engine.test.ts`:\n\n- strict legacy `assemble()` retries without `sessionKey`, `prompt`, and `runtimeSettings`\n- strict legacy `bootstrap()` retries without `runtimeSettings`\n- strict legacy `maintain()` retries without `runtimeSettings`\n- strict legacy `afterTurn()` retries without `runtimeSettings`\n- strict legacy `compact()` retries without `runtimeSettings`\n\nRuntime-settings proof added in `runtime-settings.test.ts` and `context-engine-lifecycle.test.ts`:\n\n- `model.family` defaults to `null` and never mirrors a concrete model id\n- explicit `modelFamily` is preserved when supplied\n- `fallbackReason` forces `fallbackActive: true` and `runtime.mode: \"fallback\"`\n- `degradedReason` yields `runtime.mode: \"degraded\"`\n- invalid host capabilities fail closed with `ContextEngineRuntimeSettingsUnsupportedError`\n\n## Compatibility and Risk\n\n`runtimeSettings` remains optional on every lifecycle hook param. Engines that ignore it continue unchanged. Engines with strict unknown-field validation now get the same compatibility retry behavior OpenClaw already uses for legacy `sessionKey` and `prompt` additions.\n\nRemaining risk: ClawSweeper previously asked for configured context-engine plugin proof on the latest head. This update includes current-head source-level lifecycle proof and contract proof, but not a live Gateway artifact. If configured-plugin evidence remains required, that should be captured as a separate current-head artifact before merge.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-index.test.ts src/context-engine/context-engine.test.ts src/context-engine/runtime-settings.test.ts src/agents/harness/context-engine-lifecycle.test.ts` -> pass, 63 tests total.\n- `pnpm check:test-types` -> pass.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.contracts-plugin.config.ts --maxWorkers=1` -> pass, 893 tests total.\n- `pnpm build` -> pass.\n- `git diff --check` -> clean.\n\n## Operator Understanding\n\nragesaq asked for proof from actual use before merge, called out that labels still required proof/triage proof, then asked for PR follow-up and cleanup. The stale PR body and earlier overclaim have been corrected: addressed findings now point to current-head commits and validation, and unresolved proof/scope risk is stated directly instead of hidden.",
